    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-05T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-05T07:00:00-05:00" n="775"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">367N.1113 Cottin, Max/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-05T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 5, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 5—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have today obtained from police authorities information that the Mendel Kotin
                    officially reported killed in Tiberias massacre of October 2 by Arab insurgent
                    was Max Cottin, see application for registration August 4, 1938. His wife also
                    killed to whom he was recently married here does not appear to have been an
                    American. He is first American victim of last 2½ years Palestine
                    disturbances.</p>
                <p>Political director of Jewish Agency emphasizing “unspeakable horror” of such
                    outrages and “unpardonable procrastination” of <pb facs="0958" n="950"
                        xml:id="pg_950"/> authorities stresses urgent need for more effectively
                    implementing Jewish proposals for additional arming, see despatch 787 [<hi
                        rend="italic">727</hi>], September 20.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
